  "plainText": "Don't Starve\nTogether\nExclusive to:\nSeafood Gumbo\nFood Info\n37.5\n40\n20\nMeat\nObject Info\n10 Days\nCan be Burned\n40\nCooking Info\n>2 x2-1\n20 sec\n10\nMiscellaneous\n\"seafoodgumbo\"\n“It's a jumbo seafood gumbo.”\n–Wilson\n“Ew, what IS this?”\n–Willow\n“This will make very strong Wolfgang!”\n–Wolfgang\n“A sea once teeming with life. No more.”\n–Wendy\n“READY FOR INGESTION”\n–WX-78\n“I can feel the heartburn already!”\n–Wickerbottom\n“We don't have this back home.”\n–Woodie\n“It looks passable.”\n–Maxwell\n“Still contains the skeletal remains of a fish.”\n–Wagstaff\n“A meal fit för a queen.”\n–Wigfrid\n“We could eat it forever!”\n–Webber\n“My favorite!”\n–Walani\n“Incredible! Just like Nana used to make!”\n–Warly\n“Down th'hatch!”\n–Woodlegs\n“'TIS EATS O' THE SEA”\n–Wilba\n“Mmm...”\n–Wormwood\n“Swell. Fish bones soup.”\n–Wheeler\n“Sticks to yer ribs!”\n–Winona\n“Gleefully gilly gumbo!”\n–Wortox\n“Fish looks so sad in there...”\n–Wurt\n“Packed full of flavour!”\n–Walter\n“Again... is leaving the bones in really necessary?”\n–Wanda\nSeafood Gumbo is a Crock Pot recipe introduced in the Shipwrecked DLC. It requires more than 2.0 units of Fish.\nAdding Ice will yield Ceviche instead, unless a Wobster is also added, which will yield Lobster Bisque. Adding Meats value 2.5 or higher will yield Surf 'n' Turf instead. Adding a Wobster and Butter will yield Lobster Dinner instead. Adding exactly 2 Seaweed will yield California Roll instead. Adding a Shark Fin will yield Shark Fin Soup instead. Adding Barnacles will yield Stuffed Fish Heads instead. Adding Meats value 1.5 or higher and Tallbird Egg or Fried Tallbird Egg may yield Bacon and Eggs instead. Adding more than one Monster Foods, such as Jellyfish, may yield Monster Lasagna instead. Adding Corn, single Twig or Mandrake may respectively yield Fish Tacos, Fishsticks or Mandrake Soup instead.\nIn DST, using at least 1 Eel is mandatory, otherwise the resulting meal will be Surf 'n' Turf which requires 2.5 Meat value. Currently, Eel is the only Fish with a Meat value inferior to its Fish value.\nIt restores 40 Health, 37.5 Hunger and 20 Sanity. The Health and Hunger restoration is comparable to Fishsticks, though the Sanity restoration is much higher. Seafood Gumbo can be given to the Yaarctopus in exchange for a Cloth Sail.\nPrerequisites[edit | edit source]\nRequires:\nRecipes[edit | edit source]\n>2.0\nExamples[edit | edit source]\n×2\n×3\n×2\n50% chance to yield Fishsticks.\n×3\nExchange[edit | edit source]\nTrivia[edit | edit source]\nSeafood Gumbo was introduced to Don't Starve Together in the Hook, Line, and Inker update.\nBy TypeBy Crock Pot Value\nView or edit this template\nFood and Edible Items (by Food Type)\nVeggie\nSeeds\nMeat\nGoodies\nGeneric\nHorrible\nRoughage\nElementals\nBurnt\nRaw\nGears\nGold Dust\nBerry\nWood\nNitre\nLunar Shards\nView or edit this template\nFood and Edible Items (by Food Value)\nMeats\nFishes\nVegetables\nFruits\nMonster Food\nEggs\nDairy\nSweetener\nFrozen\nInedibles\nMagic\nFat\nSeed\nJellyfish\nBone\nFilter\nAntihistamine\nDecoration\nBug\nNo Value Food",
